---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
---

<PageLayout title="Space!" description="You found it.">
  <Container>
    <div class="space-y-6 animate">
      <div class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-steel/85">Space!</div>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-black/75 font-serif">
        <p>You clicked the satellite, which means I'll let you in on a little secret. I'm a huge space geek 🚀</p>
        <p>I'm talking staying up until 3am to watch a Falcon 9 booster land. Knowing the difference between a Hohmann transfer and a bi-elliptic transfer. Having opinions about the Space Shuttle program that nobody asked for. Getting genuinely emotional when Voyager 1 crossed the heliopause.</p>
        <p>There's something about space that short-circuits every other anxiety I have. The scale of it — the sheer, incomprehensible vastness — has a way of making everything else feel appropriately small. Bad day? There are 200 billion stars in this galaxy alone. Stressed about a deadline? Somewhere out there is a neutron star spinning 700 times per second.</p>
        <p>I care about all of it: the history (Mercury, Gemini, Apollo — the whole arc), the current era (ISS, Artemis, commercial launch), the future (Mars, the outer planets, what comes after). I think the most important thing humanity could do right now is become a multi-planetary species, not because Earth is disposable but because putting all of our eggs in one pale blue dot is bad risk management.</p>
        <p>One day I'll write more here. Mission breakdowns. Launch recaps. The occasional rant about why we should have gone back to the Moon decades ago. For now, just know that the satellite orbiting that hexagon wasn't an accident. ⬢</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</PageLayout>
